Yukio Mishima’s The Sailor Who Fell from Grace with the Sea is a dark little novella set in Yokohama. A 13-year-old, Noboru, idolises Ryuji, a merchant sailor dating his widowed mother. To Noboru and his secret gang, the sea means purity and destiny—adult love is ‘compromise.’
When Ryuji gives up the sea to settle down, they feel betrayed and take that belief to a chilling extreme. It’s about hero-worship, masculinity, and how idealism can curdle into cruelty.
